==Hetu Protocol==

"Unlike traditional blockchains that rely on objective consensus, Hetu introduces "intersubjective consensus," which allows network participants to reach agreement based on shared subjective recognition. This mechanism is applicable to areas like data value, machine learning model performance, and other domains that cannot be objectively measured using traditional methods, making it ideal for AI and scientific collaboration scenarios."

(Telegram message by 'Claire')

